# CODEOWNERS
#
# Code owners are automatically added as PR reviewers.
# When a code owner opens a PR they can self-approve (no extra review needed)
# — this is how senior devs get the "1 approval" requirement waived on GitHub.
#
# Format: <path pattern>  <@github-username or @org/team>
#
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# ── Global owners (senior devs) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# These users are required reviewers for every PR.
# They can also self-approve their own PRs.
#
# Replace with real GitHub usernames:
# * @your-org/senior-devs
